<section id='project-overview'>
  <h3>Project Overview</h3>
  <section class='indent'>
    <p>
      This is a 7-day, solo project during Mod 2 of
      <%= link_to 'Turing School', "https://turing.edu/" %>'s Back End Engineering
      Program.
    </p>
    <p>
      This project builds off an existing Ruby on Rails app and adds
      functionality to create and review pet adoption applications.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can find the initial project repo here:
      <%= link_to 'Initial Project Repo', "https://github.com/turingschool-examples/adopt_dont_shop" %>
    </p>
  </section>
</section>

<section id='learning-goals'>
  <h3>Learning Goals</h3>
  <section class='indent'>
    <p>
      The learning goals of this project were as follows:
      <ul>
        <li>Build out CRUD functionality for a many to many relationship</li>
        <li>Use ActiveRecord to write queries that join multiple tables of data together</li>
        <li>Use MVC to organize code effectively, limiting the amount of logic included in views and controllers</li>
        <li>Validate models and handle sad paths for invalid data input</li>
        <li>Use flash messages to give feedback to the user</li>
        <li>Use partials in views</li>
        <li>Use within blocks in tests</li>
        <li>Track user stories using GitHub Projects</li>
        <li>Deploy an application to Heroku</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </section>
</section>

